Vapor currently won't use any of the middleware when no middleware is supplied in a config file:

``` swift
let drop = Droplet(
    staticServerMiddleware: [
        /* custom middleware here */
    ])
```

Is this the intended behavior? If not, this PR fixes that

This PR aims to make configuring the `Droplet` easier by allowing most properties to be changed and by making `Settings` configuration opt-in.

Fixes #620 
## Before

``` swift
let drop = Droplet(workDir: workDir, hash: sha512, availableMiddleware: ["auth": auth])
```
## Now
### Hardcoded

``` swift
let drop = Droplet(workDir: workDir)
drop.hash = sha512
drop.middleware.append(auth)
```
### Configuration

``` swift
let drop = Droplet(workDir: workDir)
drop.addConfigurable(hash: sha512, name: "my512")
drop.addConfigurable(middleware: auth, name: "auth")
```

`Config/crypto.json`

``` json
{
    "crypto": {
        "hash": { "method": "my512" }
    }
}
```

`Config/middleware.json`

``` json
{
    "server": ["auth"]
}
```
